[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering ByteBuddy exceptions**\n\nI'm thinking about adding a new file and wondering if ByteBuddy in native could throw an UnsupportedFeatureError as an exception. It seems like DynamicClassLoading might trigger an UnsupportedOperationException instead of an Error, which means I have to catch that differently. I know I can't just swallow RuntimeExceptions in native due to missing metadata. So, I’m really weighing if ByteBuddy’s dynamic class generation could throw that UnsupportedOperationException.\n\n**Investigating class definition issues**\n\nI’m encountering an error when defining the class. It seems that the Mocker wraps exceptions in RuntimeException, which means that the nullary load’s Exception won't catch an Error. For the variadic case, the load error seems to propagate an Error. I should test catching the Error. I wonder if the NativeImageSupport dependency is necessary. It might be useful to search for plugin info, particularly about \"org.graalvm.internal.tck\" to see what’s available.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0cc38e29b32187fb016a3538ff3b048197b7c0cf480a4dfffa\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqNTkTXHF8rvgis0NCwGvk6KQIkG7ZUaETNwDMvLYz8PCB6bJu6j_1zFXsT8Qcbbzki3LENYBkuSTNt0nV0rYIdxY-Q-TbA3johEGKng6Z-yXRbxVer3nqFGywnh-sUxt9zlzC9KS08cksycW3JStMU7SQbPQUjoToqVGRmeMWuXsOVQMXcMviN-O6WLuKlSQnRHDSt6z19F2B0JnUzV_Fd4RGy2ockEzuTPajzdhy_PACHKvwiv1eQ78EN3lDzKDl8vnPJIxT0K4M5f_XsOr7uQI6UKwII6e0sfRmYVMR7qa7eMu8C1lCx2fAQegu_zt2NZNzyqWrFfA-qO0OG4PtWkQU7QE569J2H6EmLs9tHqLYi6NTxY6GrWuKmepCQshzlQSp0uUSKmQ_uJRQpcQgtB-xdhFzEQ5d39AHq8c3eK0oh5G7BwY2vlTEevqwyruvV9Q9u-mgjfpzPTJQz30_bfftoKus6GAyUB7m0cIqG9vsJkz0LBP7vl6nPGlnfkpL0lxurCgTTSyWeDEG4UrqiJvoXpAmt0KIbNo9ZdSnleBlpOqSJzafQ50fwpI3b-KTTqX9CX6nTrdlEqMT1IPl6R8jJFjoQ9gdyKqyvuGgnwfXnnHLwSaYWjwKRqgsciGK3USNYk3CcwloQ2GJJYtxhu1Dt565cfvwI46g9q057pfi2t4CxJNjZPY3a084-7PljGuqNOdU