ructor strategy, which may create a public one invoking Object. \\n\\nAdditionally, I need to mention that no tests were run as instructed. Wait, the developer emphasized not to compile or run tests, which I will follow. I’ll ensure to include file paths in my final report.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for `org.hibernate.processor.validation.Mocker`.\n\nChanges:\n- Added dedicated test file:\n  - `tests/src/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-processor/7.2.6.Final/src/test/java/org_hibernate_orm/hibernate_processor/MockerTest.java`\n- Removed placeholder scaffold test:\n  - `tests/src/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-processor/7.2.6.Final/src/test/java/org_hibernate_orm/hibernate_processor/Hibernate_processorTest.java`\n\nCoverage targeted:\n- `Mocker.nullary(...)` + `Supplier.get()` to reach `Class#newInstance()`\n- `Mocker.variadic(...)` to reach `Class#getDeclaredConstructors()`\n- `Mocker.make(...)` to reach `Constructor#newInstance(Object[])`\n\nThe tests use `Mocker` through its public API and include the sanctioned `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(...)` handling for Byte Buddy’s runtime class generation under Native Image.\n\nI did not run compilation or tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0cc38e29b32187fb016a353985309c8197b894fd89fb832c1d\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 381, "output": 1102, "cacheRead": 20480, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21963, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781872998456, "responseId": "resp_0cc38e29b32187fb016a3539672b2881979e889d6ab37242bc"}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring test coverage and errors**\n\nI recognize that the active test coverage report expects a file for each class in MockerTest, which is good. I should consider including the UnsupportedFeatureError exception for dynamic class loading. Mocker.load generates a new class after the native build, which is interesting. I wonder if NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError is available on the JVM since it is included in the TCK. It seems that native image errors would occur as exceptions inside RuntimeException due to unsupported features, but Mocker.nullary only catches Exceptions, not Errors. However, ByteBuddy might throw an IllegalStateException that wraps the UnsupportedFeatureError.\n\n**Evaluating constructor issues**\n\nI’m wondering if there's a hidden issue with `Class.newInstance()`, which requires a zero-arg constructor. The ByteBuddy generated for an interface might have a package-private constructor. But for interface subclasses, the generated class could have a public default constructor. I'll examine ByteBuddy's default constructor strategy, which may create a public one invoking Object. \n\nAdditionally, I need to mention that no tests were run as instructed. Wait, the developer emphasized not to compile or run tests, which I will follow. I’ll ensure to include file paths in my final report.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0cc38e29b32187fb016a353967d7ac819789319cf5932620f7\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqNTmFMMYiLjxb-alIF4KzawzUKM0oi5elJlqJPde5uGGV7nibpYYdFAQT56jdbgguBnfboKAd8k6z36TOyQ659vGiMKyNdRZrNtSpO-C-XSJAmgf204D8-3cl-6jaziHdQVkFf6fzDJ8M9GseAJNVyVC79uk14kNhkCX6vk0DnqTq4M0SI0jFm0LlEQUK_lHDdeG0qH-qPEMJ1WF0CSJJzK06IXbwiWweGOYPN1Ujs6JmU0-rqeBkgpDxoqWhkgf3L-CCHQGnj4vkhiggNepNHO4gvqbzIVlErnDvKMVIOGzz1xuWYbpAzSet7pZzV5CbGzyAd5K_cZ8JfNR7zc7PBD9o35yHw0_d0-tjttZDHYYRW6znyovjDjjqiHZSFNeOseJmuu6EF-9YEj