tor strategy, which may create a public one invoking Object. \\n\\nAdditionally, I need to mention that no tests were run as instructed. Wait, the developer emphasized not to compile or run tests, which I will follow. I’ll ensure to include file paths in my final report.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for `org.hibernate.processor.validation.Mocker`.\n\nChanges:\n- Added dedicated test file:\n  - `tests/src/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-processor/7.2.6.Final/src/test/java/org_hibernate_orm/hibernate_processor/MockerTest.java`\n- Removed placeholder scaffold test:\n  - `tests/src/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-processor/7.2.6.Final/src/test/java/org_hibernate_orm/hibernate_processor/Hibernate_processorTest.java`\n\nCoverage targeted:\n- `Mocker.nullary(...)` + `Supplier.get()` to reach `Class#newInstance()`\n- `Mocker.variadic(...)` to reach `Class#getDeclaredConstructors()`\n- `Mocker.make(...)` to reach `Constructor#newInstance(Object[])`\n\nThe tests use `Mocker` through its public API and include the sanctioned `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(...)` handling for Byte Buddy’s runtime class generation under Native Image.\n\nI did not run compilation or tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0cc38e29b32187fb016a353985309c8197b894fd89fb832c1d\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 381, "output": 1102, "cacheRead": 20480, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21963, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781872998456, "responseId": "resp_0cc38e29b32187fb016a3539672b2881979e889d6ab37242bc"}, "toolResults": []}
